 \sum_{n=1}^∞ \frac{n}{2^n} =2 \ And\ \sum_{n=1}^∞ \frac{1}{2^n} =2 
k\in \mathbb{N}
 \sum_{n=1}^∞ \frac{1}{k^n} =\frac{k}{k-1}=\sum_{n=1}^∞ \frac{n}{k^n}
 \sum_{n=1}^∞ \frac{n}{2^n}
\sum_{n=1}^∞ \frac{1}{2^n} 
\sum_{n=1}^∞ \frac{1}{2^n} =2
\sum_{n=1}^∞ \frac{1}{2^n} =1
n=0
\sum_{n=0}^∞ \frac{1}{2^n} =2
 \sum_{n=0}^∞ \frac{n}{2^n}
\sum_{n=1}^∞ \frac{1}{2^n} 
\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \frac{1}{k^{n}} = \frac{1}{k}(1+\frac{1}{k}+\frac{1}{k^{2}}+...) = \frac{1}{k} \frac{1}{1-\frac{1}{k}} = \frac{1}{k-1},
\implies\sum_{r=1}^\infty\frac r{2^r}=\frac12\sum_{r=1}^\infty\frac r{2^{r-1}}=\frac12\cdot\frac1{\left(1-\dfrac12\right)^2}=2
\sum_{r=1}^\infty{a^r}= \frac a{1-a}
